usage: error_analysis.py [-h] [--out-dir OUT_DIR] [--use-context]
                         [--no-optimized-thresholds] [--skip-inference]
                         [--predictions-dir PREDICTIONS_DIR]
                         [--batch-size BATCH_SIZE] [--device DEVICE]
                         [--min-support MIN_SUPPORT]
                         [--min-confidence MIN_CONFIDENCE]
                         [--from-csv FROM_CSV] [--xlsx-dir XLSX_DIR]
                         [--xlsx XLSX] [--xlsx-homophobie XLSX_HOMOPHOBIE]
                         [--xlsx-obesite XLSX_OBESITE]
                         [--xlsx-racisme XLSX_RACISME]
                         [--xlsx-religion XLSX_RELIGION]

EMOTYC Error Analysis Pipeline (modular)

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --out-dir OUT_DIR     Output directory
  --use-context         Use neighboring sentences as context
  --no-optimized-thresholds
                        Fixed 0.5 threshold instead of optimized
  --skip-inference      Skip inference, load from pre-computed JSONL
  --predictions-dir PREDICTIONS_DIR
                        Directory with pre-computed JSONL predictions
  --batch-size BATCH_SIZE
  --device DEVICE
  --min-support MIN_SUPPORT
                        Minimum support for FP-Growth
  --min-confidence MIN_CONFIDENCE
                        Minimum confidence for association rules
  --from-csv FROM_CSV   Load a pre-computed analysis_data.csv (skips inference
                        + metrics)
  --xlsx-dir XLSX_DIR   Directory containing the 4 input XLSX files. Supports
                        both golds/ and new_golds/ layouts.
  --xlsx XLSX           Override one XLSX path with DOMAIN=PATH. Repeatable.
  --xlsx-homophobie XLSX_HOMOPHOBIE
                        Explicit XLSX path for Homophobie
  --xlsx-obesite XLSX_OBESITE
                        Explicit XLSX path for Obésité
  --xlsx-racisme XLSX_RACISME
                        Explicit XLSX path for Racisme
  --xlsx-religion XLSX_RELIGION
                        Explicit XLSX path for Religion
